<SLUG> BC-TEN-ACURA-NOTEBOOK-WRITETHRU-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SERENA GOOD ENOUGH
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
ADDS SELES 
By JOE STEVENS  
 c.1998 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Though it appears that two Williams sisters, Venus and Serena,
are on the Corel WTA tour, there actually are three sisters ---
Venus, Good Serena and Bad Serena.
</P>
<P>
   Good Serena Williams showed up Thursday in the Acura Classic at
Manhattan Country Club and beat seventh-seeded Sandrine Testud,
6-4, 3-6, 6-1. The match could have been a sign that Serena
Williams' split personality, or inconsistency, is gone.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Bad Serena has been eradicated,'' Williams said.
</P>
<P>
   Signs of Bad Serena showed up in the second set, when Williams
trailed, 4-1. But she fought back and did not go lightly. Testud
had 13 set points before she finally won the second set.
</P>
<P>
   Next, Williams takes on top-ranked and top-seeded Martina Hingis
this afternoon in the quarterfinals. Williams, ranked 21st, is in
her first tournament in six weeks and appears stronger and steadier
than when she played last. So does she have a shot at winning?
</P>
<P>
   ``I think so,'' Williams said. ``It depends on which Serena
shows up.''
</P>
<P>
   Fourteen-ranked Testud thinks so, too. ``She thinks she can beat
anyone, so it makes it even harder to beat her,'' Testud said.
</P>
<P>
   Seles comes back in second set
</P>
<P>
   Fourth-seeded Monica Seles advanced to the semifinals by beating
fifth-seeded Nathalie Tauziat, 6-4, 6-4, in one hour and four
minutes. Seles trailed, 4-1, in the second set, but rattled off
five straight games to win.
</P>
<P>
   Seles now is 9-0 against Tauziat in her career. In the
semifinals, she will face the winner of tonight's 7 p.m. match
between second-seeded Lindsay Davenport and eighth-seeded Natasha
Zvereva.
</P>
<P>
   Lucky loser wins again
</P>
<P>
   Elena Tatarkova, who earned a spot in the tournament when Mary
Pierce withdrew, advanced to the quarterfinals with a win over
sixth-seeded Irina Spirlea, 6-2, 6-2. Tatarkova, ranked 63rd, will
face third-seeded Arantxa Sanchez Vicario in the quarterfinals.
</P>
<P>
   Two teams in semifinals
</P>
<P>
   Two doubles teams, Hingis with Natasha Zvereva and Chanda Rubin
with Irina Spirlea have advanced to the semifinals. Two
quarterfinal matches will be played today.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By The PRESS TELEGRAM, LONG BEACH, CALIFORNIA
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
