<SLUG> BC-BBN-GALAXY-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GALAXY WINS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By FRED J. ROBLEDO  
 c.1998 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR; PASADENA--One minute Carlos Hermosillo's eyes were rolling with
relief--the next minute, he was pumping his fists to the crowd
after scoring the fastest consecutive goals in MLS history, only 64
seconds apart in the 76th and 78th minutes.
</P>
<P>
   His two goals helped lead the Galaxy to a playoff clinching 3-0
victory over Kansas City, in front of 10,200 at the Rose Bowl
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Hermosillo, all but tar and feathered for going his first 10
games without scoring a goal after coming to L.A. heralded as
Mexico's all-time leading scorer, certainly looked like a player
whose career was starting over again.
</P>
<P>
   His two goals added more significance, because his first goal
put L.A. in a tie with D.C. United for the most goals in the
regular season, and his second, the 71st of the season for the
Galaxy, established the MLS team scoring record.
</P>
<P>
   The victory clinched Los Angeles' third consecutive playoff
berth in as many seasons and they are now just a couple victories
shy of nailing down their second Western Conference regular season
title in three years.
</P>
<P>
   Still, all the talk centered around Hermosillo, who was given a
good luck stone by the Galaxy's fan club (the Galaxians) a day
earlier. Hermosillo walked into the presroom sporting a bright
yellow Galaxian shirt afterward.
</P>
<P>
   ``These fans have always supported me from the first day I
walked on the turf, Hermosillo said. ``This one was for them. I
consider myself a Galaxian.
</P>
<P>
   Someone asked if Hermosillo had ever gone this long without
scoring a goal before.
</P>
<P>
   ``Not even in my dreams, he said. ``When you don't score goals
and you have a lot of opportunities you begin to doubt yourself. I
started to doubt myself just a little bit but thanks to my
teammates and the fans who never lost support in me I began to come
through.
</P>
<P>
   Following his first goal, Hermosillo put his finger in front of
his mouth, a message he said, to quiet his critics.
</P>
<P>
   ``There have been a lot of people over time who have been
talking about me, Hermosillo said. ``I was just telling them to be
quiet and have some patience. The second goal was more for the
people who have supported me since I've come here.
</P>
<P>
   Galaxy coach Octavio Zambrano, not particularly pleased with the
overall flow of the game, was glad Hermosillo put those goals
behind him.
</P>
<P>
   ``Obviously I'm glad he finally got that off his mind, Zambrano
said. ``Anytime a goal scorer breaks out of a slump, that's reason
to be happy.
</P>
<P>
   The Galaxy's league leading mark improved to 19-6 (55 points)
with six games remaining. Second place Chicago (13-10, 37 points)
now trails L.A. by 18 points, with nine games left on its schedule.
</P>
<P>
   Kansas City, who was swept in all four meetings with L.A. this
season, dropped to 10-12.
</P>
<P>
   Los Angeles, who had its problems creating chances throughout
the game, particularly in the first half, saw defender Robin Fraser
at one point make a 70-yard run that almost resulted in a goal.
</P>
<P>
   Fraser's run probably sparked the Galaxy offense, because the
league's top scoring machine surprised Kansas City in the 32nd
minute to take a 1-0 lead, thanks to a tremendous burst of speed
from Cobi Jones.
</P>
<P>
   At the bottom of the center-circle in the Galaxy's own half of
the field, midfielder Martin Machon dropped a 35-yard pass over
three Kansas City defenders who turned to scramble for the ball,
but Jones simply sprinted past them, leaving himself one-one-one
with Wizard goalkeeper Mike Ammann. The K.C. keeper hurried out to
challege Jones, but the Galaxy midfielder easily beat him to the
right side for his 13th goal of the season.
</P>
<P>
   -30-
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By The SAN GABRIEL VALLEY TRIBUNE, WEST COVINA,
CALIFORNIA
</P>
</TEXT>
