wreck, racing on a country road. Hump-hopping, they call it.
</P>
<P>
   These tragedies never feel like just another headline. They hit
us hard. All that promise, lost in an instant. (McCarty, Dayton
Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MINTER-COLUMN _ HUNGRY HORSE, Mont. _ Late one afternoon last
month I came in from the garden to discover my wife in a state of
ecstasy. ``Guess what?'' she announced. ``Alex and Judy have
invited us to go with them on a trip retracing the Lewis and Clark
expedition!'' Won't happen, I said. (Minter, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
