<P>
   LIFESTYLE (l category)
</P>
<P>
   WARNER-ON-WOOD _ ATLANTA _ For woodworkers with boundless energy
and an overwhelming interest in equipment, the International
Woodworking Machinery and Furniture Supply Fair is almost upon us.
It opens Thursday at the Georgia World Congress Center and runs
through Aug. 23. MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TEST-DRIVE _ ATLANTA _ The German/American automaker BMW reaches
a milestone this month when the 100,000th of its ``brand within a
brand'' M-Series vehicles comes off the assembly line at its Greer,
S.C., plant. (DeVault, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED. (l, f)
</P>
<P>
   SHARP-DRIVING _ ATLANTA _ When auto experts talk about
``alternative'' vehicles, they are usually referring to those
powered by natural gas or electricity. But you might also consider
a nontraditional vehicle as an alternative. (Sharp, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED. (l, f)
</P>
<P>
   THE-MECHANIC _ ATLANTA _ Adhering to the manufacturer's
specification for fuel octane is not a condition limited to the
owners of ``high performance'' vehicles. It is just as important
for the rest of us to heed the octane requirements of the cars we
drive. (Carter, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED. (l, f)
</P>
<P>
   SCRAPBOOKS _ Family photo albums take on a new look when
creative people put their mind to it. (Ricardo, Austin
American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   CELEBRITY-CLOTHES _ ``I'll never wash this dress again!'' Why do
we shriek for a rock star's sweaty T-shirt, a piece of an
Ayatollah's shroud, any item that has been sullied by a famous
person? We pose the question to those in the know, find out if
there's value in acquiring these items and lists some famous
garments that have _ or have not _ been worth acquiring. (Anna,
Palm Beach Post).
</P>
<P>
   TABLETOP-DESIGN _ When 50 designers agree to host a dinner
party, you can bet the heat will be on to push the table design
over the top. Such will be the case Aug. 27 when the Atlanta
chapter of DIFFA _ Design Industries Foundation Fighting AIDS _
hosts ``Collection Rouge II: Dining By Design.'' The fund-raising
dinner combines nine traveling three-dimensional tabletop designs
by nationally renowned designers with 41 created by local talents.
(Flanders, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). ETA: 5 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   DESIGN-LIST _ A list of designers participating in Dining by
Design. (Flanders, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). ETA: 5 p.m.
</P>
<P>
