gallons a year to keep a lush landscape. What about folks on the
other end that go to extraordinary lengths to conserve water.
Talking to the Sierra Club, Xeriscape group, Earth First, etc., to
identify three of them for mini-profiles of 8 inches each. (Martin,
Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   TIPS _ Water saving tips submitted by readers. (Martin, Austin
American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   RELIGION
</P>
<P>
   RELIGION-BOATS _ At 8:50 every Sunday morning between Memorial
Day and Labor Day the boats come into sight _ pontoon craft,
runabouts and ski boats _ skimming across the glimmering water like
bugs. Officially called Lake Rabun Leisure Ministries, boat church
is a 27-year tradition of Clayton's First United Methodist Church.
(White, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). ETA: 5 p.m.
</P>
