events, focusing on the drama of conflict and the revelations of
people at their worst. No bit of recent history brings this home
more forcefully than ``The Rape of Nanking'' by Iris Chang
(Blackstone Audiobooks, 9 nine hours). (Stafford, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED. Eds: This is a monthly column.
</P>
