<HEADLINE>
EDITORS:
</HEADLINE>
  
 Friday, Aug. 14, 1998      The Hearst News Service will file the following stories for
Saturday and Sunday. If you have questions, call Tim Spence at
202-298-6920.  
    (Slugline includes the ``HNS'' tag.)
   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   JET-SKIS (San Francisco) _ San Francisco officials are looking
to ban the use of Jet Skis and other personal watercraft from
within 1,200 of the city's shoreline _ a move that backers hope
will trigger a wave of other Bay Area counties to crackdown on the
popular vessels. By RACHEL GORDON.
</P>
<P>
   AREA-CODES (San Francisco) _ California, which had no telephone
area codes at all in 1947, is about to get its 23rd _ and you ain't
seen nothin' yet. By ERIC BRAZIL.
</P>
<P>
   LUBY-OBIT (San Antonio) _ Robert M. ``Bob'' Luby, founder of a
cafeteria that evolved into a multimillion-dollar chain serving
