<P>
   ISLAND-DISCOVERY (Washington) _ The discovery of pristine coral
reefs on the shores of a virtually unknown American-owned island is
a chance for the United States to mend a ``melancholy record
worldwide of coral reef history,'' Secretary of the Interior Bruce
Babbitt said Friday. Scientists recently returned from a two-week
expedition to the remote Caribbean island territory. By NICOLE
TSONG.
