<HEADER>
A4325 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-HOT-TIPS-LADN     08-14 0519
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HOT-TIPS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WOMEN LOVE HARRISON FORD, CANDLELIGHT AND SOAP
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BARBARA DE WITT 
c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ &UR;  &LR; It's no big surprise that Harrison Ford was voted
the sexiest man alive ... or that ``Ally McBeal'' was rated the
sexiest TV show in a national poll of women readers for InStyle
magazine.
</P>
<P>
   But perfume manufacturers might get their noses out of joint
learning that the sexiest scent in America is ... soap.
</P>
<P>
   The survey also reported young women like daredevils over
bookworms, candle-lit dinners over picnics, power over money and
think firemen have the sexiest job.
</P>
<P>
   FILE UNDER `BARE-CHESTER HUNKS': Speaking of buffed babes, Miz
Hot Tips discovered a bunch of them _ right out of Playgirl
magazine _ on nail files. It's a novelty collection called Man
Files from Toma Industries in North Hollywood that features color
photos of bare-chested hunks, including Scott Lane, Playgirl
magazine's 1998 Man of the Year. Each photo is bonded to a durable
Mylar surface that's washable and is priced at $3 at nail salons or
directly from the company. For younger girls, the company also
makes nail files with happy faces and teddy bears. For more
information, call (800) 843-4606.
</P>
<P>
   SHOPPER'S ALERT: Love St. John knit suits and Ferragamo pumps
but can't afford them? Miz Hot Tips learned that the Discovery
Shop, 4454 Van Nuys Blvd., Sherman Oaks, received a huge collection
of hardly worn, recent designs by St. John, as well as Donna Karan,
Christian Dior, Lily Rubin and Nolan Miller, all in larger sizes,
including 12 and 16. Plus Ferragamo shoes.
</P>
<P>
   And they're on sale today from 10 a.m. until midnight for about
a fourth of the original price. All proceeds benefit the American
Cancer Society's Valley projects.
</P>
<P>
   YOU'RE SO MOODY: Remember those mood rings that were supposed to
register your true feelings? You know, blue for incredibly happy,
brown for feelin' just OK?
</P>
<P>
   The Estee Lauder company must be in a nostalgic mood, as its
latest novelty is the Attitude Compact, a small powder-filled
compact that changes color to reveal your mood (happy, sad, tense)
in 10 seconds. Miz Hot Tips tried it and found that it took more
like 15 or 20 seconds to turn it from black to blue, but maybe she
was in a bad mood ...
</P>
<P>
   Anyway, it's way cute and could provide a conversation op for
life's awkward moments, like first dates or when you're trapped in
a stalled elevator with a dozen strangers. Look for them at
department stores, priced at $32.50.
</P>
<P>
   HOW PERSONAL: Back in the '60s, a number of pop singers wrote
songs about girls they adored, but you probably weren't one of
them. Neither was Miz Hot Tips. So she was thrilled about a new Los
Angeles-based company called Song for You. For $59.95, they'll
create a shiny gold CD with your (or a loved one's) name on it, and
provide a song _ pop, country or opera _ all about you, using
information you provide. They have a variety of witty
special-occasion songs for birthdays and anniversaries, too. For
more information, call (800) 789-7664.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
