turned out to be both unworkable and dangerous.
 &HT;    It is a source of political instability, engendering
irresponsible behavior and confrontation between the branches of
government.
 &HT;    I also propose submitting to the referendum a constitutional
amendment creating a post of life-long senator for former
presidents after they leave office. Such an initiative would help
to ease this very dramatic moment, avoiding a dangerous division in
Russian society and assuring a democratic transition from one team
to another.
 &HT;    The time has come for the president to prove that Russia's
interests and stability and, above all, the interests of its people
are indeed his highest priority.
 &HT;     c.1998 LaStampa  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; (Mikhail Gorbachev, the last leader of the Soviet Union before
its collapse in 1991 and Nobel Peace Prize winner, now heads the
Gorbachev Foundation, a political think tank in Moscow, with a new
office at Northeastern University, in Boston. He also writes a
monthly commentary column for La Stampa, a newspaper in Turin,
Italy.) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   -------------------- &QC;
</P>
</TEXT>
