political crisis, the blindingly bright economic picture of the
past couple of years suddenly looks murkier. What makes things a
bit scary is that the economy has now shifted into much slower
gear. And slowdowns _ which make it harder for businesses and
consumers to shrug off random blows _ have a way of turning into
recessions. By Sylvia Nasar.
