<P>
   &QL;  PA Contract Awards States News Service Washington, August 14
-- News Printing Co. of Claysburg won a $145,174 contract from the
Government Printing Office in Washington, D.C., for printing
services.
</P>
<P>
   Braceland Brothers Inc. of Philadelphia won a $106,903 contract
from the Government Printing Office in Washington, D.C., for
printing services.
</P>
<P>
   Fry Communications Inc. of Mechanicsburg won a $608,310 contract
from the Government Printing Office in Washington, D.C., for
printing services.
</P>
<P>
   Stein Seal Co. of Kulpsville won a $1.3 million contract from
the Tinker Air Force Base in Oklahoma for engineering services.
</P>
<P>
   Fidler Brothers Construction Co. of Pottsville won a $51,300
contract from the Dept. of Justice in Washington, D.C., for
construction services.
</P>
<P>
   Boeing Co. of Ridley Park won a $231,715 contract from the
Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio, for aircraft components.
</P>
<P>
   Penn State Tool and Die Corp. of Irwin won a $112,160 contract
from the Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio, for aircraft
equipment.
</P>
<P>
   Wiler Corp. of Cresco won a $76,667 contract from the General
Services Administration in Kansas City, Mo., for hand tools.
</P>
<P>
   Merck Vaccine Division of West Point won a $131 million contract
from the Center for Disease Control and Prevenion in Atlanta, Ga.,
for medical supplies.
</P>
<P>
   Grip-Flex Corp. of Philadelphia won a $126,360 contract from the
Defense Personnel Support Center in Philadelphia for clothing
equipment.
</P>
