<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Braves on deck: Los Angeles Dodgers
 &HT;    By Thomas Stinson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   When: 4:05 p.m. EDT
</P>
<P>
   Where: Dodger Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   TV: FOX.
</P>
<P>
   Probable starting pitchers: RHP John Smoltz (10-2, 3.36; 13-11,
2.85 lifetime vs. Dodgers) vs. RHP Chan Ho Park (10-6, 3.90; 2-0,
3.86 lifetime vs. Braves).
</P>
<P>
   Notes: Last time out, Smoltz was hit as hard as he has been all
year, giving up six hits and five runs _ two of them Barry Bonds
homers _ on Sunday in San Francisco. Until then, he had been superb
during seven-straight starts _ 12 earned runs allowed in 46 innings
_ while going 5-0. Despite the worries about his right elbow,
Smoltz has struck out 70 batters in his 66 2/3 innings since coming
back from the DL on June 20. His 8.9 strikeouts per nine innings
would rank fourth in the league if Smoltz had pitched enough
innings to qualify. He has not faced the Dodgers this year but was
2-1 against them last season. He is 6-7 lifetime at Dodger Stadium.
Park, 25, had gone seven weeks without a loss until his last
outing, when he allowed two runs to Pittsburgh in a 2-1 loss. With
Ramon Martinez out, he has emerged as the ace of the staff,
although he has yet to throw a complete game this season. His ERA
is somewhat high, but it has been on a steady decline since
cresting at 5.36 in late June. Park rattled off 48 innings while
allowing just seven earned runs and going 5-0 during that period.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
