<P>
   (NYT23) DOVER, N.H. -- Aug. 14, 1998 -- CLINTON-NH-VOICES-3,
8-14 -- New Hampshire residents are voicing yet another chorus of
defiant indifference to allegations that Clinton may have had
sexual contact with Monica Lewinsky. I think it's terrible for our
nation and I truly think it's not doing us any good around the
world,'' says Inez DiMambro, right, a 68-year-old housewife and
mother. ``He's the president,'' says shopping companion Diane King.
``He should act more presidential.'' (Rick Friedman/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT22) DOVER, N.H. -- Aug. 14, 1998 -- CLINTON-NH-VOICES-2,
8-14 -- Many New Hampshire residents are tired of hearing that
Clinton may have had sexual contact with Monica Lewinsky.
``Ultimately, I think it's a travesty that people don't have better
things to do with this country than to investigate whether the
president is sleeping with obviously more-than-willing partners,''
says construction laborer David Pierce, center. ``How about let's
talk about something really important - the New York Yankees!''
(Rick Friedman/New York Times Photo) *LITE
</P>
